article.description: Zane Najdawi scored 26 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and The Citadel rolled to a 146-84 victory over Division II member Johnson University of Florida on Sunday.
article.headline: The Citadel rout Johnson University 146-84
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Zane Najdawi scored 26 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and The Citadel rolled to a 146-84 victory over Division II member Johnson University of Florida on Sunday. It was the most The Citadel has scored since beating Bob Jones 121-111 in 2015. The Bulldogs made 46 of program record 107 shots, its most since making 50 against Coker in 1984 and 1985. The Bulldogs shot 102 field goals against USC Aiken in 1982. Najdawi was 8 of 13 from the floor and made 10 of 11 free throws. Matt Frierson had 21 points and five steals. Brian White had 18 points, and Preston Parks and Warren Sledge had 10 assists apiece. Josh Grover scored 21 points to lead Johnson. Douet Broughton added 18 points and Caleb Winfrey chipped in 15. The Bulldogs had a double-digit lead midway through the first half.
